"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/632040","Department for International Trade","false","2016-11-18","<p>UK Export Finance has not supported any new deliveries of Airbus aircraft since January 2016.</p><p>UK Export Finance is working with Airbus and the French and German export credit agencies to understand and seek assurances around Airbus's practices with regard to overseas agents. In the meantime UK Export Finance remains open to applications from any UK exporter, including Airbus, subject to conducting appropriate due diligence on compliance issues.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2016-11-18T10:48:17.557Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/632040/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/632040/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/632040/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2016-11-08","Airbus: Export Credit Guarantees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, on what date UK Export Finance started a temporary freeze of Airbus export credit cover; and whether that freeze is still in place.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","52298"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/632041","Department for International Trade","false","2016-11-14","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer given by my rt hon. Friend the Member for Broxtowe (Anna Soubry) on 29 June 2016, UIN (41073).</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2016-11-14T17:52:50.343Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/632041/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/632041/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/632041/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2016-11-08","Overseas Investment: Treaties","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, if he will take steps to ensure that Parliament has the opportunity to scrutinise all future bilateral investment treaties.","false","Biography information for Thangam Debbonaire","Bristol West","Thangam Debbonaire","52439"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/632042","Department for International Trade","false","2016-11-17","<p>The UK is signatory to over 90 bilateral investment treaties (BITs). Until the UK leaves the EU, we will remain subject to EU trade &amp; investment agreements and policy.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2016-11-17T16:46:12.697Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/632042/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/632042/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/632042/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2016-11-08","Overseas Investment: Treaties","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what steps his Department is taking to develop a framework for bilateral investment treaties to be implemented when the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Royston Smith","Southampton, Itchen","Royston Smith","52404"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/632043","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2016-11-15","<p>The Government is determined to get the best possible deal for the UK’s future customs and trading relations with the EU. The Department for Exiting the European Union is considering the full range of possible tariff and non-tariff barriers to trade across all areas of importance to the UK economy, and assessing ways in which these might be addressed.</p><p>The Prime Minister has committed to working closely with the Welsh Government, together with the Scottish Government and Northern Ireland Executive, as work continues to analyse the options to ensure that we get the best possible deal for all parts of the United Kingdom.</p>The Welsh Government will have every opportunity to have their say as we form our negotiating strategy. This includes through the new Joint Ministerial Committee on EU Negotiations, which brings together constituent parts of the United Kingdom to develop a UK-wide approach to our negotiations. At the Committee’s first meeting on 9 November, Ministers set out their priorities for discussion at future meetings and agreed to develop further the proposed work programme to ensure its connection to and involvement with the process of negotiations.","Clwyd West","Mr David Jones",,"2016-11-15T13:53:51.577Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/632043/answer","Biography information for Mr David Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/632043/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/632043/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2016-11-08","Employment: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what assessment the Government has made of the potential effect of EU tariffs and non-tariff barriers on jobs in Wales when the UK leaves the Single Market and Customs Union.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Edwards","Carmarthen East and Dinefwr","Jonathan Edwards","52390"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/632044","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2016-11-14","<p>Details of Ministers' meetings will be published on a quarterly basis as is standard practice.</p><p> </p>","Clwyd West","Mr David Jones",,"2016-11-14T13:53:30.373Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/632044/answer","Biography information for Mr David Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/632044/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/632044/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2016-11-08","Higher Education: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, pursuant to the Answer of 3 November 2016 to Question 51228, on higher education: Scotland, when the Department's quarterly transparency returns and details of meetings held since the Department's formation will be published.","false","Biography information for Seema Malhotra","Feltham and Heston","Seema Malhotra","52229"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/632045","HM Treasury","false","2016-11-14","<p>The UK is a member of the EIB through its EU membership. The UK’s future relationship with the EIB will be part of the EU exit negotiations. The government will not provide a running commentary on the options for that future relationship as it seeks the best deal for the UK.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-11-14T11:02:39.867Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/632045/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/632045/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/632045/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-11-08","European Investment Bank","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the possible options are for the UK's future relationship with the European Investment Bank.","false","Biography information for Seema Malhotra","Feltham and Heston","Seema Malhotra","52214"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/632046","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2016-11-14","<p>The Prime Minister has been clear we will not give a running commentary on preparations for Brexit negotiations. We will ensure that we engage closely with all relevant interlocutors.</p><p> </p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2016-11-14T14:01:34.17Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/632046/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/632046/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/632046/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2016-11-08","European Investment Bank","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what recent meetings his Department has had with representatives of the European Investment Bank.","false","Biography information for Seema Malhotra","Feltham and Heston","Seema Malhotra","52219"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/632399","Department for Education","false","2016-11-21","<p>We have made a commitment to allow employers to transfer digital funds to other employers in their supply chains, sectors or communities in 2018. We have suggested that this should initially be set at 10 per cent.</p><p> </p><p>We have created a new employer working group, including the Charities Finance Group, to help us further develop proposals for a transfers system that works for employers. Alongside detailed research into the needs of employers of all sizes, this group will help us design how transfers should work, the level of funds that could be transferred and what controls are needed to protect the integrity of the apprenticeship system.</p><p> </p><p>Unlike other taxes, levied employers can get back their contributions if they are committed to training sufficient numbers of high-quality apprentices. They will also receive a top up of 10 per cent on their digital funds.</p><p> </p><p>There has been no specific assessment of the amount registered charities and private sector employers paying the Apprenticeship Levy will lose as a result of funds in their digital account expiring because the employer was unable to spend them. Last month we announced an extension to the period employers will have to spend their digital funds, from 18 to 24 months.</p><p> </p><p>We have published estimates of levy payments, and apprenticeship spending, by sector in the attached document.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Nash","HL3071 ; HL3074","2016-11-21T15:45:54.767Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/632399/answer","Biography information for Lord Nash","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/632399/answer","HL3070 HL3071 HL3074 attachment.pdf","HL3070 HL3071 HL3074 attachment.pdf","Information_on_apprenticeship_levy","Information_on_apprenticeship_levy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/632399/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-11-08","Apprentices: Taxation","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of the impact on the charity sector of the proposal to limit the proportion of the annual value of a qualifying employer's Apprenticeship Levy funding pot that can be transferred to another employer to 10 per cent.","false","Biography information for Lord Aberdare",,"Lord Aberdare","HL3070"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/632400","Department for Education","false","2016-11-21","<p>We have made a commitment to allow employers to transfer digital funds to other employers in their supply chains, sectors or communities in 2018. We have suggested that this should initially be set at 10 per cent.</p><p> </p><p>We have created a new employer working group, including the Charities Finance Group, to help us further develop proposals for a transfers system that works for employers. Alongside detailed research into the needs of employers of all sizes, this group will help us design how transfers should work, the level of funds that could be transferred and what controls are needed to protect the integrity of the apprenticeship system.</p><p> </p><p>Unlike other taxes, levied employers can get back their contributions if they are committed to training sufficient numbers of high-quality apprentices. They will also receive a top up of 10 per cent on their digital funds.</p><p> </p><p>There has been no specific assessment of the amount registered charities and private sector employers paying the Apprenticeship Levy will lose as a result of funds in their digital account expiring because the employer was unable to spend them. Last month we announced an extension to the period employers will have to spend their digital funds, from 18 to 24 months.</p><p> </p><p>We have published estimates of levy payments, and apprenticeship spending, by sector in the attached document.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Nash","HL3070 ; HL3074","2016-11-21T15:45:54.83Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/632400/answer","Biography information for Lord Nash","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/632400/answer","HL3070 HL3071 HL3074 attachment.pdf","HL3070 HL3071 HL3074 attachment.pdf","Information_on_apprenticeship_levy","Information_on_apprenticeship_levy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/632400/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-11-08","Apprentices: Taxation","2","House of Lord