"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631065","HM Treasury","false","2016-11-14","<p>Treasury Ministers and officials have meetings with a wide variety of organisations in the public and private sectors to discuss a broad range of topics in the process of policy development and delivery.</p><p> </p><p>Details of ministerial meetings with external organisations on departmental business are published on a quarterly basis and are available at:</p><p> </p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/hmt-ministers-meetings-hospitality-gifts-and-overseas-travel</p>","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby",,"2016-11-14T11:11:17.463Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631065/answer","Biography information for Simon Kirby","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631065/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631065/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-11-07","Sovereign Wealth Funds","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what discussions have taken place between the Government and managers of global sovereign wealth funds since the vote for the UK to leave the EU; and if he will make available the agendas of those meetings.","false","Biography information for Ian Murray","Edinburgh South","Ian Murray","52121"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631066","HM Treasury","false","2016-11-14","<p>It has been possible for eligible couples to claim the Marriage Allowance since September 2015. 305,861 couples successfully claimed Marriage Allowance in 2015 and, to date, a further 763,377 couples have successfully applied in 2016. Eligible couples who haven’t claimed for the 2015/16 tax year are able to do so until 5 April 2020.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2016-11-14T17:02:10.513Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631066/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631066/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631066/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-11-07","Married People: Tax Allowances","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, pursuant to the Answer of 1 November 2016 to Question 51521, on marriage tax allowances, how many couples have taken up the marriage tax allowance in each year since its introduction.","false","Biography information for Tim Farron","Westmorland and Lonsdale","Tim Farron","52103"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631067","HM Treasury","false","2016-11-14","<p>Childcare vouchers can only be used to pay for qualifying childcare which is registered or approved. Vouchers can be used to pay for approved childcare on school premises, provided it is outside of school hours for children who have reached compulsory school age. School residential trips do not qualify as registered or approved childcare because they occur outside of the school premises. The government does not have any plans to extend the use of childcare vouchers.</p><p> </p><p>Parents in receipt of certain benefits are exempt from paying the cost of board and lodging for residential school visits.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-11-14T16:07:18.303Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631067/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631067/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631067/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-11-07","Child Care Vouchers: Extracurricular Activities","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, for what reasons parents are unable to use childcare vouchers to pay for the cost of a school residential trip; and if he will amend the rules to permit parents to do so.","false","Biography information for Tim Loughton","East Worthing and Shoreham","Tim Loughton","52189"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631068","HM Treasury","false","2016-11-14","<p>I refer the hon. Member to today’s Written Ministerial Statement “Update on HMRC’s contract with Concentrix”.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","52193 ; 52194","2016-11-14T16:55:16.393Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631068/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631068/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631068/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-11-07","Concentrix","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, with reference to the contract between HM Revenue and Customs and Concentrix, Appendix 1, Clause G2.1A(a), whether the contractor accrued the relevant number of service points across consecutive measurement periods needed to trigger Clause G2.1A.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","52192"
