"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631219","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-11-17","<p>The Safety in Custody statistics, including assaults on prison staff and prisoners and self-harm incidents, are published quarterly, and establishment level data are updated annually. The latest bulletin was published on 27 October 2016 and can be found on gov.uk.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2016-11-17T11:31:58.783Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631219/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631219/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631219/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-11-07","Bedford Prison","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many (a) assaults on staff (b) assaults on prisoners and (c) self-harm incidents occurred at HMP Bedford in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","52182"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631220","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-12-19","<p>Improving safety and decreasing violence in prisons is a key priority. Last month we launched the Prison Safety and Reform White Paper and we are already implementing measures to tackle drugs, drones and phones. This major overhaul of the prison system will include the recruitment of an extra 2,500 frontline officers. Our reforms will empower governors to make the changes they need, ensuring that prisons are places of safety and reform.</p><p>225 prisoners were removed from HMP Bedford following the disturbance on 6 November 2016. 140 cells required repair. A programme of works was immediately put in place to bring cells back into operation as soon as possible.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2016-12-19T19:11:18.02Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631220/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631220/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631220/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-11-07","Bedford Prison","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many (a) prisoners have been removed from and (b) cells require repair in HMP Bedford after the disturbance on 6 November 2016.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","52183"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631221","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-12-20","<p>The work of HM Inspectorate of Prisons (HMIP) is vital to our prison system. We have taken immediate action to address the recommendations made by HMIP.</p><p>Additional resources are being provided to help HMP Bedford to improve safety, including the introduction of body worn cameras, upgraded CCTV, and HMP Bedford will also receive additional staff as part of plans to increase staffing levels across the estate.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2016-12-20T17:58:01.823Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631221/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631221/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631221/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-11-07","Bedford Prison","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what steps her Department plans to take to ensure that recommendations by HM Inspectorate of Prisons in its February 2014 and May 2016 inspections into HMP Bedford are put into effect.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","52184"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631222","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-11-14","<p>I wrote to the hon. Member on behalf of the Secretary of State on 7 November, providing details of the policy and practice in prisons and in courts to make appropriate provision for women offenders who wish to breastfeed or express milk.</p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee",,"2016-11-14T11:38:19.313Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631222/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631222/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631222/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-11-07","Members: Correspondence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, when she plans to respond to the letter from the hon. Member for Glasgow Central on 14 September 2016 regarding breastfeeding and the expressing of breast milk for female offenders.","false","Biography information for Alison Thewliss","Glasgow Central","Alison Thewliss","52061"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631223","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-11-18","<p>As part of the programme of work to improve the civil enforcement process we will have due regard to data protection responsibilities.</p>","North East Hertfordshire","Sir Oliver Heald",,"2016-11-18T12:46:59.403Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631223/answer","Biography information for Sir Oliver Heald","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631223/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631223/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-11-07","Companies: Disclosure of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, pursuant to the Answer of 17 October 2016 to Question 47208, if her Department will ensure that commercial companies do not have access to sensitive information as part of their considerations on how to improve the civil enforcement process.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","52077"
