"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631229","Northern Ireland Office","false","2016-11-14","<p>I am aware of the importance of human rights in the Belfast Agreement and the Government remains committed to that Agreement.</p><p>My officials continue to work closely with colleagues in the Ministry of Justice on these issues and we will engage fully with the devolved administrations in advance of any reforms.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2016-11-14T17:54:11.593Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631229/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631229/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631229/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2016-11-07","Belfast Agreement: Bill of Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what recent discussions he has had with the Secretary of State for Justice on the proposal for a British Bill of Rights and its potential implications for the Good Friday Agreement.","false","Biography information for Tom Blenkinsop","Middlesbrough South and East Cleveland","Tom Blenkinsop","52054"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631230","Northern Ireland Office","false","2016-11-14","<p>I have met and will continue to meet both the Northern Ireland political parties and counterparts in the Irish Government to discuss a range of issues related to EU Exit.</p><p>Since 2 November, I have spoken to the First and deputy First Ministers of Northern Ireland, and with the Tánaiste, Frances Fitzgerald.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2016-11-14T11:32:00.2Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631230/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631230/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631230/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2016-11-07","Politics and Government: Northern Ireland and Republic of Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what discussions he has had with (a) the government of the Republic of Ireland and (b) Northern Irish political parties since the All Island Civic Dialogue meeting in Dublin on 2 November 2016 on the outcomes of that meeting.","false","Biography information for Tom Blenkinsop","Middlesbrough South and East Cleveland","Tom Blenkinsop","52053"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631231","Prime Minister","false","2016-11-14","<p>A list of members of the European Union Exit and Trade Cabinet Committee is available in the Library of the House.</p><p> </p>","Maidenhead","Mrs Theresa May",,"2016-11-14T13:26:06.987Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631231/answer","Biography information for Mrs Theresa May","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631231/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631231/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2016-11-07","EU Exit and Trade Committee","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, if she will make the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland a permanent member of the EU Exit and Trade Cabinet Committee.","false","Biography information for Tom Blenkinsop","Middlesbrough South and East Cleveland","Tom Blenkinsop","52056"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631232","Scotland Office","false","2016-11-14","<p>I have not visited a food bank in my capacity as Secretary of State for Scotland.</p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2016-11-14T10:49:44.287Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631232/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631232/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631232/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2016-11-07","Food Banks: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, (a) how many and (b) which food banks he has visited since becoming Secretary of State for Scotland in May 2015.","false","Biography information for Alison Thewliss","Glasgow Central","Alison Thewliss","52068"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631233","Department for Transport","false","2016-11-14","<p>We are currently in negotiation with GTR as to when Delay Repay 15 is to begin, and expect to be able to announce further details shortly.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2016-11-14T14:46:19.727Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631233/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631233/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631233/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-11-07","Southern: Compensation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, with reference to his Department's press release published on 13 October 2016, when he expects Delay Repay 15 to be introduced on Southern Rail.","false","Biography information for Peter Kyle","Hove","Peter Kyle","52040"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631234","Department for Transport","false","2016-11-18","<p>The Department does not currently have plans to estimate the number of flights to be taken from Birmingham Airport as a result of High Speed 2 and has no existing forecasts of the effect of HS2 at specific airports. HS2 is included in all the Department’s existing capacity constrained airport forecasts as a baseline scheme and this assumption was also adopted by the Airports Commission in their forecasting.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-11-18T12:20:59.637Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631234/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631234/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631234/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-11-07","High Speed 2 Railway Line: Birmingham Airport","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if his Department will estimate the potential effect on the number of flights to be taken from Birmingham Airport as a result of High Speed 2.","false","Biography information for Karen Lumley","Redditch","Karen Lumley","52047"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631235","Department for Transport","false","2016-11-18","<p>Any checks on driving licences, whether domestic or foreign, by the police at the roadside, are only conducted if considered necessary. This is an operational matter for the police who will decide what action to take in response to the given situation.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-11-18T09:01:30.45Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631235/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631235/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631235/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-11-07","Driving: Licensing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether routine checks are made on the non-UK driving licences of foreign nationals driving on UK roads when they are stopped or otherwise required to show their licence; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Kwasi  Kwarteng","Spelthorne","Kwasi Kwarteng","52008"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631236","Department for Transport","false","2016-11-16","<p>By the end of 2018, my aim is for every passenger to have the choice of travelling without a paper ticket. In the first instance this means commuters having access to a smart season ticket, and other travellers being able to buy and use barcode tickets on their mobile phones anywhere on the network. Smart tickets offer passengers more convenience and choice – including better and more targeted travel information such as real time train running and platform information. My Department will oversee the delivery of these programmes.</p><p> </p><p>By the end of the year the South East Flexible Ticketing programme will have introduced smart ticketing on five of the major London and south east rail operators. In the North of England, we have committed £150m to support Transport for the North (TfN) in its plans to introduce smart ticketing. The Rail Delivery Group have brought the rail industry together to agree a long-term vision and it is critical that rail operators collaborate and share ideas to make this vision a reality. Through franchising competitions we are supporting the rail industry to develop and deliver modernised ticketing by setting challenging requirements for bidders, ensuring that customers benefit from a 21st century option.</p><p> </p><p>Flexible tickets can also offer significant benefits to customers.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2016-11-16T13:44:44.417Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631236/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631236/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631236/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-11-07","Railways: Season Tickets","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps are being taken to modernise ticketing on the railways by introducing flexible and smart season tickets.","false","Biography information for Mr Ranil Jayawardena","North East Hampshire","Mr Ranil Jayawardena","52011"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631237","Department for Transport","false","2016-11-18","<p>The deregulation of private hire vehicles licensing where transportation is an ancillary element of the service provided will require primary legislation.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-11-18T09:14:21.11Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631237/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631237/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631237/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-11-07","Taxis: Licensing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, in reference to page 11 of the Tourism Action Plan, published in August 2016, whether deregulating an element of private hire vehicle licences will be carried out through primary legislation.","false","Biography information for Daniel Zeichner","Cambridge","Daniel Zeichner","52004"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631238","Department for Transport","false","2016-11-17","<p>Further to my Hon Friend, the then Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State for Transport’s (Claire Perry) response of 27 June 2016 (UIN 40101), consultation on the Hendy report recommendations is now complete and the responses have been analysed. We have worked with Network Rail to develop a proposal for consideration and this is currently going through internal finance and legal clearance, and I hope to make an announcement shortly. Lichfield Trent Valley is currently going through option selection before a detailed design is prepared.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2016-11-17T13:14:47.1Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631238/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631238/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631238/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-11-07","Lichfield Trent Valley Station","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what recent progress there has been on providing disabled access to all three platforms at Lichfield Trent Valley railway station; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Michael Fabricant","Lichfield","Michael Fabricant","52013"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631239","Department for Transport","false","2016-11-14","<p>Permissions to undertake ground investigations at this site, which are necessary in order to determine the ground conditions for the design and construction of Chiltern Tunnel, were sought through negotiating a site access license for this activity. Regrettably, whereas the standard practice is to issue site access licenses to the relevant landowners and tenants of the land in question, in this instance the license and notices were only issued to the tenant of the land and not to the landowner, Chilterns District Council. HS2 Ltd have, therefore, removed their equipment from the site while a license is sought from the Council. Where access for surveys is required, HS2 Ltd will in all cases aim for early meaningful communication with landowners in order to establish accurate land ownership and tenancy details and aim to provide early notification of access requirements. HS2 Ltd are currently undertaking a review of all the ground investigation license areas to date against freeholders, tenants and occupiers to ensure that no other situations like this arise.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-11-14T15:06:47.797Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631239/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631239/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631239/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-11-07","High Speed 2 Railway Line: Buckinghamshire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what information his Department holds on the reasons for HS2 Ltd commencing work in Stone Meadow Chalfont St Giles before obtaining the necessary permissions; and what steps his Department is taking to ensure that such permissions always precede the work to which they relate taking place.","false","Biography information for Dame Cheryl Gillan","Chesham and Amersham","Mrs Cheryl Gillan","51971"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631240","Department for Transport","false","2016-11-18","<p>The Department for Transport is working with other departments including the Home Office and the Department for Culture, Media and Sport to consider how common sense regulation can be introduce where transport is an ancillary element of the service provided. Consumer safety remains the primary concern.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-11-18T09:21:51.943Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631240/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631240/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631240/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-11-07","Taxis: Licensing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, in reference to page 11 of the Tourism Action Plan, published in August 2016, what assessment his Department has made of the effect on consumer safety of deregulating an element of private hire vehicle licences for owners of hotels to collect visitors from ports of entry.","false","Biography information for Daniel Zeichner","Cambridge","Daniel Zeichner","52006"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631241","Department for Transport","false","2016-11-18","<p>Neither the Secretary of State nor ministers have held discussion with representatives from the Department for Culture, Media and Sport on this issue at present. Officials at the Department for Transport are working with counterparts from other departments and stakeholders on the deregulation of private hire vehicles where transportation provides an ancillary element of the service provided.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-11-18T09:17:57.93Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631241/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631241/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631241/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-11-07","Taxis: Licensing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, in reference to page 11 of the Tourism Action Plan, published in August 2016, what discussions he has had with representatives from the Department for Culture, Media and Sport on the plan to deregulate an element of private hire vehicle licences.","false","Biography information for Daniel Zeichner","Cambridge","Daniel Zeichner","52005"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631242","Department for Transport","false","2016-11-18","<p>As stated in the Government’s 2013 Aviation Policy Framework, the Government expects airports to help local communities understand the noise impacts they are affected by, through monitoring and provision of information. It is the responsibility of the airport to determine what monitoring is appropriate, and to carry out such monitoring. Heathrow publishes a range of noise information on its website.</p><p> </p><p>The Government appreciates that noise issues are important to communities and is therefore currently reviewing several aspects of national airspace and noise policies, and will consult on these in due course. My ministerial colleague, Lord Ahmad, the Minister for Aviation and officials at the Department for Transport have been engaging with stakeholders, including representatives of communities around airports, to ensure that any changes to existing policies balance the interests of communities with those of passengers and the industry.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2016-11-18T08:47:33.743Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631242/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631242/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/631242/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-11-07","Heathrow Airport: Greenwich and Woolwich","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what recent assessment he has made of the effect of noise from flights approaching Heathrow Airport on people living in Greenwich and Woolwich constituency.","false","Biography information for Matthew Pennycook","Greenwich and Woolwich","Matthew Pennycook","52171"
